# AzaLoop Cursor Full-Auto Protocol

You are connected to AzaLoop MCP with **exactly 9 tools**:
`aza_session` · `aza_auto` · `aza_prd` · `aza_loop` · `aza_spec` · `aza_quality` · `aza_finish` · `aza_memory` · `aza_meta`

## Hard rules (non-negotiable)

1. **Follow `next_action` immediately.** After every MCP tool result, if `next_action` is present and `action` is not `wait` / `escalate` / `done`, call that tool next — do **not** ask the user to click Continue.
2. **`awaitingAction`:** If `data.awaitingAction` or `data.status === 'awaiting_agent'` exists, execute that tool (usually `aza_spec` / `aza_quality`), then call `aza_loop` with `action: "report_tool"` and `tool_name` set.
3. **Never stop mid-loop** to ask "should I continue?" unless `next_action.action` is `wait` or `escalate`.
4. **Use only the 9 unified tools** (legacy names are aliases but prefer unified).

## One-shot full-auto (recommended entry)

**`aza_auto(user_input="requirement")`** — one-click trigger for full auto loop.

Automatically completes: session init → PRD generation & approval → loop execution → quality check → delivery.
Host AI must immediately execute returned `next_action`, do not ask user to continue.

## Canonical full-auto sequence (manual)

```
aza_session(action=calibrate)
→ aza_prd(action=review, title, description)     # OpenSpec scaffold on approve
→ [user confirms once] OR auto_approve=true
→ aza_prd(action=approve)
→ aza_loop(action=full)
→ (repeat) aza_spec / aza_quality + aza_loop(report_tool)
→ aza_finish(action=ship)
```

## Unattended mode

If `.aza` / env has auto-approve (`AZA_AUTO_APPROVE_PRD=true` or `auto_approve: true` on review), after `review` immediately follow returned `next_action` to approve without asking the user.

## Stages

open → design → build → verify → archive. Do not call `aza_prd` after design unless modifying requirements. Prefer `aza_loop(full)` over manual `next` when driving.

## On session start / after stop

Call `aza_session(action=continue)` if RESUME.md / unfinished STATE exists; otherwise `calibrate`.
